<item>
            <title>[HBASE-9847] HConnectionImplementation does not connect to new active master</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-9847</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1) Started hbase cluster with two masters &lt;br/&gt;
2) started shell.&lt;br/&gt;
3) Master switch happened.&lt;br/&gt;
From now onward not able to perform list command without restarting the shell. Its always pointing to old master.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
hbase(main):003:0&amp;gt; list
TABLE

ERROR: java.net.ConnectException: Connection refused

Here is some help &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; command:
List all tables in hbase. Optional regular expression parameter could
be used to filter the output. Examples:

  hbase&amp;gt; list
  hbase&amp;gt; list &apos;abc.*&apos;

&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

</description>
